  (N n r : ℝ) / (q n : ℝ)

/--
Definition of the Discrete Fourier Transform fHat.
Define the Discrete Fourier Transform of $f$ at frequency
$h \in \mathbb{Z}/q\mathbb{Z}$ as:
  $$ \hat{f}(h) = \frac{1}{q} \sum_{x=0}^{q-1}
       f(x) e^{-2\pi i h x / q} $$
-/
